    "attributes": {
        "action": "Hold a referendum on a federal system for the UK & greater devolution in England",
        "additional_details": "We want more power to rest closer to the people. We would like the devolved English regions/provinces to reflect the historic and current identity of the people so that they can identify with their local assembly. Decisions on transport, education and healthcare should be localised under a federal system.\r\n \r\nWe want a written federal constitution to enshrine in law the relationship between a UK Federal government and the devolved regions/ provinces and nations.",
        "background": "The Government should hold a referendum on introducing a federal system for the UK, with new devolved regions or provinces to England to stand alongside devolved parliaments of Scotland, Wales and Northern Ireland.",
